/55993/TB_Gamebook.pdf Game book]\n |scoring=\n'''First quarter'''\n*TB \u2013 [[Rian Lindell]] 30-yard field goal, 1:45. ''Buccaneers 3\u20130. '''Drive: 15 plays, 73 yards, 7:06.'''''\n'''Second quarter'''\n*ATL \u2013 [[Matt Bryant]] 46-yard field goal, 12:07. ''Tied 3\u20133. '''Drive: 10 plays, 53 yards, 4:38.'''''\n*TB \u2013 [[Bobby Rainey]] 43-yard run (Rian Lindell kick), 10:14. ''Buccaneers 10\u20133. '''Drive: 4 plays, 81 yards, 1:53.'''''\n*TB \u2013 [[Mason Foster]] 37-yard interception return (Rian Lindell kick), 7:05. ''Buccaneers 17\u20133.''\n*TB \u2013 Bobby Rainey 3-yard run (Rian Lindell kick), 3:16. ''Buccaneers 24\u20133. '''Drive: 5 plays, 53 yards, 1:46.'''''\n*ATL \u2013 Matt Bryant 49-yard field goal, 0:56. ''Buccaneers 24\u20136. '''Drive: 8 plays, 49 yards, 2:20.'''''\n'''Third quarter'''\n*TB \u2013 Bobby Rainey 4-yard pass from [[Mike Glennon]] (Rian Lindell kick), 9:34. ''Buccaneers 31\u20136. '''Drive: 4 plays, 67 yards, 2:02.'''''\n*TB \u2013 [[Vincent Jackson]] 3-yard pass from Mike Glennon (Rian Lindell kick), 1:54. ''Buccaneers 38\u20136. '''Drive: 7 plays, 20 yards, 3:49.'''''\n*ATL \u2013 [[Harry Douglas]] 80-yard pass from [[Matt Ryan (American football)|Matt Ryan]] (Matt Bryant kick), 1:02. ''Buccaneers 38\u201313. '''Drive: 2 plays, 80 yards, 0:52.'''''\n'''Fourth quarter'''\n*TB \u2013 Rian Lindell 46-yard field goal, 7:15. ''Buccaneers 41\u201313. '''Drive: 9 plays, 27 yards, 6:11.'''''\n*ATL \u2013 [[Antone Smith]] 50-yard run ([[Dominique Davis]]\u2013[[Tony Gonzalez]] pass), 5:22. ''Buccaneers 41\u201321. '''Drive: 6 plays, 80 yards, 1:53.'''''\n*ATL \u2013 [[Roddy White]] 6-yard pass from Matt Ryan (Matt Bryant kick), 1:45. ''Buccaneers 41\u201328. '''Drive: 8 plays, 80 yards, 1:55.'''''\n |stats=\n'''Top passers'''\n*ATL \u2013 [[Matt Ryan (American football)|Matt Ryan]] \u2013 19/36, 254 yards, 2 TD, 2 INT\n*TB \u2013 [[Mike Glennon]] \u2013 20/23, 231 yards, 2 TD\n'''Top rushers'''\n*ATL \u2013 [[Antone Smith]] \u2013 2 rushes, 88 yards, TD\n*TB \u2013 [[Bobby Rainey]] \u2013 30 rushes, 163 yards, 2 TD\n'''Top receivers'''\n*ATL \u2013 [[Harry Douglas]] \u2013 6 receptions, 134 yards, TD\n*TB \u2013 [[Vincent Jackson]] \u2013 10 receptions, 165 yards, TD\n}}\nThe Buccaneers managed a comprehensive victory against the Falcons, improving their record to 2-8.\n\nBobby Rainey rushed for 163 yards and 2 touchdowns. Vincent Jackson caught 10 passes for 165 yards and a touchdown. Gerald McCoy had 3 sacks in the game. Mike Glennon threw for 2 touchdowns. Mason Foster and Dashon Goldson both had an interception, the former of which returned it for a touchdown. Dekoda Watson blocked a punt.\n\n====Week 12: at Detroit Lions====\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle={{NFLPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers 97thru13|border=2}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week Twelve: Tampa Bay Buccaneers at Detroit Lions&nbsp;\u2013 Game summary\n |date=November 24\n |time=1:00 p.m. EST\n |road='''Buccaneers'''\n |R1=3|R2=14|R3=0|R4=7\n |home=Lions\n |H1=0|H2=14|H3=7|H4=0\n |stadium=[[Ford Field]], [[Detroit|Detroit, Michigan]]\n |attendance=62,098\n |weather=None (indoor stadium)\n |referee=Clete Blakeman\n |TV=Fox\n |TVAnnouncers=[[Thom Brennaman]], [[Brian Billick]] and [[Laura Okmin]]\n |reference=[http://www.nfl.com/gamecenter/2013112402/2013/REG12/buccaneers@lions Recap], [http://www.nfl.com/liveupdate/gamecenter/56002/DET_Gamebook.pdf Game book]\n |scoring=\n'''First quarter'''\n*TB \u2013 [[Rian Lindell]] 38-yard field goal, 3:27. ''Buccaneers 3\u20130. '''Drive: 13 plays, 58 yards, 7:51.'''''\n'''Second quarter'''\n*DET \u2013 [[Nate Burleson]] 5-yard pass from [[Matthew Stafford]] ([[David Akers]] kick), 11:54. ''Lions 7\u20133. '''Drive: 11 plays, 80 yards, 6:33.'''''\n*TB \u2013 [[Tiquan Underwood]] 7-yard pass from [[Mike Glennon]] (Rian Lindell kick), 8:50. ''Buccaneers 10\u20137. '''Drive: 6 plays, 80 yards, 3:08.'''''\n*DET \u2013 [[Joseph Fauria]] 10-yard pass from Matthew Stafford (David Akers kick), 4:38. ''Lions 14\u201310. '''Drive: 7 plays, 80 yards, 4:09.'''''\n*TB \u2013 [[Leonard Johnson (American football)|Leonard Johnson]] 48-yard interception return (Rian Lindell kick), 1:01. ''Buccaneers 17\u201314.''\n'''Third quarter'''\n*DET \u2013 [[Brandon Pettigrew]] 18-yard pass from Matthew Stafford (David Akers kick), 9:41. ''Lions 21\u201317. '''Drive: 8 plays, 69 yards, 3:53.'''''\n'''Fourth quarter'''\n*TB \u2013 Tiquan Underwood 85-yard pass from Mike Glennon (Rian Lindell kick), 14:17. ''Buccaneers 24\u201321. '''Drive: 4 plays, 95 yards, 1:42.'''''\n |stats=\n'''Top passers'''\n*TB \u2013 [[Mike Glennon]] \u2013 14/21, 247 yards, 2 TD\n*DET \u2013 [[Matthew Stafford]] \u2013 26/46, 297 yards, 3 TD, 4 INT\n'''Top rushers'''\n*TB \u2013 [[Bobby Rainey]] \u2013 18 rushes, 35 yards\n*DET \u2013 [[Reggie Bush]] \u2013 15 rushes, 83 yards\n'''Top receivers'''\n*TB \u2013 [[Tiquan Underwood]] \u2013 3 receptions, 108 yards, 2 TD\n*DET \u2013 [[Calvin Johnson]] \u2013 7 receptions, 115 yards\n}}\nLions quarterback [[Matthew Stafford]] threw four interceptions, as Tampa Bay upset Detroit 24\u201321. The Buccaneers became the first team since 1978 to start the season 0\u20138 and win their next three games. Stafford was leading the Lions on a potential game-winning or game-tying drive in the final minute. At the Tampa Bay 28 yard line with 1:00 left, Stafford threw to [[Calvin Johnson]] at the 3 yard line. Johnson appeared to catch the ball, but it was stripped out and fell into the hands of [[Johnthan Banks]] for an interception, and sealed the win for Tampa Bay.\n\n====Week 13: at Carolina Panthers====\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle={{NFLPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers 97thru13|border=2}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week Thirteen: Tampa Bay Buccaneers at Carolina Panthers&nbsp;\u2013 Game summary\n |date=December 1\n |time=1:00 p.m. EST\n |road=Buccaneers\n |R1=6|R2=0|R3=0|R4=0\n |home='''Panthers'''\n |H1=7|H2=10|H3=7|H4=3\n |stadium=[[Bank of America Stadium]], [[Charlotte, North Carolina]]\n |attendance=72,795\n |weather=Partly cloudy, {{convert|56|F|C}}\n |referee=[[Ron Winter]]\n |TV=Fox\n |TVAnnouncers=[[Chris Myers]], [[Tim Ryan (American football, born 1967)|Tim Ryan]] and [[Jennifer Hale (sportscaster)|Jennifer Hale]]\n |reference=[http://www.nfl.com/gamecenter/2013120100/2013/REG13/buccaneers@panthers Recap], [http://www.nfl.com/liveupdate/gamecenter/56016/CAR_Gamebook.pdf Game book]\n |scoring=\n'''First quarter'''\n*TB \u2013 [[Rian Lindell]] 27-yard field goal, 9:14. ''Buccaneers 3\u20130. '''Drive: 8 plays, 59 yards, 4:27.'''''\n*CAR \u2013 [[Brandon LaFell]] 16-yard pass from [[Cam Newton]] ([[Graham Gano]] kick), 6:15. ''Panthers 7\u20133. '''Drive: 5 plays, 83 yards, 3:02.'''''\n*TB \u2013 Rian Lindell 53-yard field goal, 2:19. ''Panthers 7\u20136. '''Drive: 4 plays, \u22123 yards, 2:26.'''''\n'''Second quarter'''\n*CAR \u2013 Graham Gano 23-yard field goal, 6:26. ''Panthers 10\u20136. '''Drive: 14 plays, 76 yards, 6:05.'''''\n*CAR \u2013 Cam Newton 1-yard run (Graham Gano kick), 0:30. ''Panthers 17\u20136. '''Drive: 7 plays, 49 yards, 3:45.'''''\n'''Third quarter'''\n*CAR \u2013 [[Ted Ginn Jr.|Ted Ginn]] 36-yard pass from Cam Newton (Graham Gano kick), 10:58. ''Panthers 24\u20136. '''Drive: 4 plays, 78 yards, 2:10.'''''\n'''Fourth quarter'''\n*CAR \u2013 Graham Gano 22-yard field goal, 6:43. ''Panthers 27\u20136. '''Drive: 13 plays, 66 yards, 8:45.'''''\n |stats=\n'''Top passers'''\n*TB \u2013 [[Mike Glennon]] \u2013 14/21, 180 yards, INT\n*CAR \u2013 [[Cam Newton]] \u2013 18/29, 263 yards, 2 TD, 2 INT\n'''Top rushers'''\n*TB \u2013 [[Bobby Rainey]] \u2013 17 rushes, 63 yards\n*CAR \u2013 [[Cam Newton]] \u2013 5 rushes, 68 yards, TD\n'''Top receivers'''\n*TB \u2013 [[Vincent Jackson]] \u2013 3 receptions, 75 yards\n*CAR \u2013 [[Greg Olsen (American football)|Greg Olsen]] \u2013 5 receptions, 85 yards\n}}\nPanthers QB [[Cam Newton]] threw for 263 yards and two touchdowns while running for another touchdown, as Carolina soundly defeated Tampa Bay 27\u20136, sweeping the season series.\n\nWith the loss, the Buccaneers were mathematically eliminated from playoff contention.\n\n====Week 14: vs. Buffalo Bills====\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle={{NFLPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers 97thru13|border=2}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week Fourteen: Buffalo Bills at Tampa Bay Buccaneers&nbsp;\u2013 Game summary\n |date=December 8\n |time=1:00 p.m. EST\n |road=Bills\n |R1=3|R2=0|R3=3|R4=0\n |home='''Buccaneers'''\n |H1=14|H2=10|H3=3|H4=0\n |stadium=Raymond James Stadium, Tampa, Florida\n |attendance=59,194\n |weather=Cloudy, {{convert|82|F|C}}\n |referee=[[Bill Vinovich]]\n |TV=[[NFL on CBS|CBS]]\n |TVAnnouncers=[[Spero Dedes]] and [[Steve Beuerlein]]\n |reference=[http://www.nfl.com/gamecenter/2013120807/2013/REG14/bills@buccaneers Recap], [http://www.nfl.com/liveupdate/gamecenter/56037/TB_Gamebook.pdf Game book]\n |scoring=\n'''First quarter'''\n*TB \u2013 [[Bobby Rainey]] 80-yard run ([[Rian Lindell]] kick), 14:56. ''Buccaneers 7\u20130. '''Drive: 2 plays, 80 yards, 0:18.'''''\n*BUF \u2013 [[Dan Carpenter]] 40-yard field goal, 8:12. ''Buccaneers 7\u20133. '''Drive: 7 plays, 36 yards, 2:29.'''''\n*TB \u2013 [[Vincent Jackson]] 38-yard pass from [[Mike Glennon]] (Rian Lindell kick), 2:47. ''Buccaneers 14\u20133. '''Drive: 9 plays, 80 yards, 5:33.'''''\n'''Second quarter'''\n*TB \u2013 Rian Lindell 53-yard field goal, 10:52. ''Buccaneers 17\u20133. '''Drive: 4 plays, 6 yards, 1:32.'''''\n*TB \u2013 [[Tim Wright (American football)|Tim Wright]] 5-yard pass from Mike Glennon (Rian Lindell kick), 0:20. ''Buccaneers 24\u20133. '''Drive: 10 plays, 57 yards, 4:31.'''''\n'''Third quarter'''\n*BUF \u2013 Dan Carpenter 46-yard field goal, 10:25. ''Buccaneers 24\u20136. '''Drive: 9 plays, 52 yards, 4:41.'''''\n*TB \u2013 Rian Lindell 32-yard field goal, 0:11. ''Buccaneers 27\u20136. '''Drive: 4 plays, \u22122 yards, 0:54.'''''\n'''Fourth quarter'''\n* ''No scoring plays.''\n |stats=\n'''Top passers'''\n*BUF \u2013 [[EJ Manuel]] \u2013 18/33, 184 yards, 4 INT\n*TB \u2013 [[Mike Glennon]] \u2013 9/25, 90 yards, 2 TD, 2 INT\n'''Top rushers'''\n*BUF \u2013 [[EJ Manuel]] \u2013 5 rushes, 29 yards\n*TB \u2013 [[Bobby Rainey]] \u2013 22 rushes, 127 yards, TD\n'''Top receivers'''\n*BUF \u2013 [[Steve Johnson (American football)|Steve Johnson]] \u2013 5 receptions, 67 yards\n*TB \u2013 [[Vincent Jackson]] \u2013 3 receptions, 70 yards, TD\n}}\n[[Bobby Rainey]] scored an 80-yard rushing touchdown on the second play of the game and rushed for 127 yards total, setting the tone for the Buccaneers' decisive 27-6 thrashing of the [[2013 Buffalo Bills season|Buffalo Bills]].\n\nOn offense, [[Mike Glennon]] threw two touchdown passes, one each to [[Vincent Jackson]] and [[Tim Wright (American football)|Tim Wright]]. The Buccaneers defense had seven sacks and four interceptions, out of which [[Lavonte David]] made one sack and two interceptions. On special teams, [[Dashon Goldson]] recovered a fumble muffed by the punt returner.\n\n====Week 15: vs. San Francisco 49ers====\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle={{NFLPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers 97thru13|border=2}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week Fifteen: San Francisco 49ers at Tampa Bay Buccaneers&nbsp;\u2013 Game summary\n |date=December 15\n |time=1:00 p.m. EST\n |road='''49ers'''\n |R1=7|R2=10|R3=3|R4=13\n |home=Buccaneers\n |H1=0|H2=7|H3=0|H4=7\n |stadium=Raymond James Stadium, Tampa, Florida\n |attendance=64,142\n |weather=Cloudy, {{convert|70|F|C}}\n |referee=[[Scott Green (American football official)|Scott Green]]\n |TV=Fox\n |TVAnnouncers=Dick Stockton, Ronde Barber and Kris Budden\n |reference=[http://www.nfl.com/gamecenter/2013121508/2013/REG15/49ers@buccaneers Recap], [http://www.nfl.com/liveupdate/gamecenter/56054/TB_Gamebook.pdf Game book]\n |scoring=\n'''First quarter'''\n*SF \u2013 [[Michael Crabtree]] 4-yard pass from [[Colin Kaepernick]] ([[Phil Dawson]] kick), 7:05. ''49ers 7\u20130. '''Drive: 11 plays, 62 yards, 6:56.'''''\n'''Second quarter'''\n*SF \u2013 Phil Dawson 47-yard field goal, 6:12. ''49ers 10\u20130. '''Drive: 9 plays, 28 yards, 4:45.'''''\n*SF \u2013 [[Vernon Davis]] 52-yard pass from Colin Kaepernick (Phil Dawson kick), 1:47. ''49ers 17\u20130. '''Drive: 5 plays, 81 yards, 1:52.'''''\n*TB \u2013 [[Vincent Jackson]] 11-yard pass from [[Mike Glennon]] ([[Rian Lindell]] kick), 0:29. ''49ers 17\u20137. '''Drive: 7 plays, 80 yards, 1:18.'''''\n'''Third quarter'''\n*SF \u2013 Phil Dawson 43-yard field goal, 7:51. ''49ers 20\u20137. '''Drive: 8 plays, 19 yards, 2:59.'''''\n'''Fourth quarter'''\n*TB \u2013 [[Tim Wright (American football)|Tim Wright]] 24-yard pass from Mike Glennon (Rian Lindell kick), 14:54. ''49ers 20\u201314. '''Drive: 10 plays, 92 yards, 4:01.'''''\n*SF \u2013 Phil Dawson 21-yard field goal, 4:27. ''49ers 23\u201314. '''Drive: 17 plays, 77 yards, 10:27.'''''\n*SF \u2013 [[Kendall Hunter]] 2-yard fumble return (Phil Dawson kick), 4:21. ''49ers 30\u201314.''\n*SF \u2013 Phil Dawson 35-yard field goal, 2:49. ''49ers 33\u201314. '''Drive: 4 plays, 9 yards, 0:55.'''''\n |stats=\n'''Top passers'''\n*SF \u2013 [[Colin Kaepernick]] \u2013 19/29, 203 yards, 2 TD\n*TB \u2013 [[Mike Glennon]] \u2013 18/34, 179 yards, 2 TD, INT\n'''Top rushers'''\n*SF \u2013 [[Frank Gore]] \u2013 22 rushes, 86 yards\n*TB \u2013 [[Bobby Rainey]] \u2013 11 rushes, 27 yards\n'''Top receivers'''\n*SF \u2013 [[Vernon Davis]] \u2013 5 receptions, 79 yards, TD\n*TB \u2013 [[Tim Wright (American football)|Tim Wright]] \u2013 7 receptions, 82 yards, TD\n}}\nVincent Jackson and Tim Wright caught the only two touchdowns for the Buccaneers in the game, which were not enough to stop the 49ers from trouncing the team 33-14. On defense, [[Gerald McCoy]] and [[Adrian Clayborn]] had the only sacks for the Bucs. Late in the game, [[Eric Page]] attempted to hand the ball to [[Russell Shepard]] on a tricky play during a kick return; however, Shepard fumbled the ball, allowing the 49ers' [[Kendall Hunter]] to recover and return it for a touchdown.\n\nWith the loss, the Buccaneers' record dropped to 4-10.\n\n====Week 16: at St. Louis Rams====\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle={{NFLPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers 97thru13|border=2}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week Sixteen: Tampa Bay Buccaneers at St. Louis Rams&nbsp;\u2013 Game summary\n |date=December 22\n |time=1:00 p.m. EST/12:00 p.m. [[Central Time Zone|CST]]\n |road=Buccaneers\n |R1=7|R2=3|R3=3|R4=0\n |home='''Rams'''\n |H1=0|H2=14|H3=3|H4=6\n |stadium=[[Edward Jones Dome]], [[St. Louis, Missouri]]\n |attendance=54,423\n |weather=None (indoor stadium)\n |referee=[[John Parry (American football official)|John Parry]]\n |TV=Fox\n |TVAnnouncers=Thom Brennaman, Brian Billick and Laura Okmin\n |reference=[http://www.nfl.com/gamecenter/2013122208/2013/REG16/buccaneers@rams Recap], [http://www.nfl.com/liveupdate/gamecenter/56069/STL_Gamebook.pdf Game book]\n |scoring=\n'''First quarter'''\n*TB \u2013 [[Bobby Rainey]] 1-yard run ([[Rian Lindell]] kick), 6:31. ''Buccaneers 7\u20130. '''Drive: 11 plays, 85 yards, 4:37.'''''\n'''Second quarter'''\n*STL \u2013 [[Zac Stacy]] 1-yard run ([[Greg Zuerlein (American football)|Greg Zuerlein]] kick), 13:48. ''Tied 7\u20137. '''Drive: 13 plays, 80 yards, 7:43.'''''\n*STL \u2013 [[Stedman Bailey]] 27-yard run (Greg Zuerlein kick), 12:04. ''Rams 14\u20137. '''Drive: 1 play, 27 yards, 0:09.'''''\n*TB \u2013 Rian Lindell 35-yard field goal, 0:00. ''Rams 14\u201310. '''Drive: 9 plays, 36 yards, 4:27.'''''\n'''Third quarter'''\n*TB \u2013 Rian Lindell 32-yard field goal, 9:23. ''Rams 14\u201313. '''Drive: 9 plays, 51 yards, 3:55.'''''\n*STL \u2013 Greg Zuerlein 54-yard field goal, 5:08. ''Rams 17\u201313. '''Drive: 7 plays, 29 yards, 4:15.'''''\n'''Fourth quarter'''\n*STL \u2013 Greg Zuerlein 25-yard field goal, 11:15. ''Rams 20\u201313. '''Drive: 12 plays, 49 yards, 6:33.'''''\n*STL \u2013 Greg Zuerlein 48-yard field goal, 3:15. ''Rams 23\u201313. '''Drive: 9 plays, 29 yards, 5:52.'''''\n |stats=\n'''Top passers'''\n*TB \u2013 [[Mike Glennon]] \u2013 16/26, 158 yards\n*STL \u2013 [[Kellen Clemens]] \u2013 16/20, 158 yards\n'''Top rushers'''\n*TB \u2013 [[Bobby Rainey]] \u2013 20 rushes, 37 yards, TD\n*STL \u2013 [[Zac Stacy]] \u2013 33 rushes, 104 yards, TD\n'''Top receivers'''\n*TB \u2013 [[Vincent Jackson]] \u2013 5 receptions, 98 yards\n*STL \u2013 [[Stedman Bailey]] \u2013 3 receptions, 44 yards\n}}\nOn offense, Bobby Rainey scored the Bucs' only touchdown of the game. On defense, Gerald McCoy had a sack. Also Adrian Clayborn and Dekoda Watson both forced fumbles which Lavonte David and Keith Tandy both successfully recovered for the Buccaneers, though the offense was only able to get a field goal out of the resulting possessions.\n\n====Week 17: at New Orleans Saints====\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle={{NFLPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers 97thru13|border=2}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week Seventeen: Tampa Bay Buccaneers at New Orleans Saints&nbsp;\u2013 Game summary\n |date=December 29\n |time=4:25 p.m. EST/3:25 p.m. CST\n |road=Buccaneers\n |R1=7|R2=7|R3=3|R4=0\n |home='''Saints'''\n |H1=14|H2=14|H3=7|H4=7\n |stadium=[[Mercedes-Benz Superdome]], [[New Orleans, Louisiana]]\n |attendance=73,150\n |weather=None (indoor stadium)\n |referee=[[Carl Cheffers]]\n |TV=Fox\n |TVAnnouncers=Thom Brennaman, Brian Billick and Laura Okmin\n |reference=[http://www.nfl.com/gamecenter/2013122908/2013/REG17/buccaneers@saints Recap], [http://www.nfl.com/liveupdate/gamecenter/56085/NO_Gamebook.pdf Game book]\n |scoring=\n'''First quarter'''\n*NO \u2013 [[Lance Moore]] 44-yard pass from [[Drew Brees]] ([[Shayne Graham]] kick), 10:15. ''Saints 7\u20130. '''Drive: 9 plays, 80 yards, 4:45.'''''\n*TB \u2013 [[Tiquan Underwood]] 48-yard pass from [[Mike Glennon]] ([[Rian Lindell]] kick), 8:40. ''Tied 7\u20137. '''Drive: 4 plays, 62 yards, 1:35.'''''\n*NO \u2013 [[Jimmy Graham]] 10-yard pass from Drew Brees (Shayne Graham kick), 3:08. ''Saints 14\u20137. '''Drive: 9 plays, 80 yards, 5:32.'''''\n'''Second quarter'''\n*NO \u2013 [[Robert Meachem]] 41-yard pass from Drew Brees (Shayne Graham kick), 8:04. ''Saints 21\u20137. '''Drive: 5 plays, 57 yards, 1:29.'''''\n*TB \u2013 [[Tim Wright (American football)|Tim Wright]] 1-yard pass from Mike Glennon (Rian Lindell kick), 3:28. ''Saints 21\u201314. '''Drive: 9 plays, 80 yards, 4:36.'''''\n*NO \u2013 [[Kenny Stills]] 76-yard pass from Drew Brees (Shayne Graham kick), 2:40. ''Saints 28\u201314. '''Drive: 3 plays, 80 yards, 0:48.'''''\n'''Third quarter'''\n*TB \u2013 Rian Lindell 54-yard field goal, 6:35. ''Saints 28\u201317. '''Drive: 13 plays, 44 yards, 8:25.'''''\n*NO \u2013 [[Pierre Thomas (American football)|Pierre Thomas]] 8-yard run (Shayne Graham kick), 1:22. ''Saints 35\u201317. '''Drive: 10 plays, 92 yards, 5:13.'''''\n'''Fourth quarter'''\n*NO \u2013 Drew Brees 9-yard run (Shayne Graham kick), 14:08. ''Saints 42\u201317. '''Drive: 4 plays, 25 yards, 2:05.'''''\n |stats=\n'''Top passers'''\n*TB \u2013 [[Mike Glennon]] \u2013 22/41, 219 yards, 2 TD, INT\n*NO \u2013 [[Drew Brees]] \u2013 24/31, 381 yards, 4 TD\n'''Top rushers'''\n*TB \u2013 [[Brian Leonard]] \u2013 5 rushes, 35 yards\n*NO \u2013 [[Khiry Robinson]] \u2013 12 rushes, 50 yards\n'''Top receivers'''\n*TB \u2013 [[Tiquan Underwood]] \u2013 5 receptions, 93 yards, TD\n*NO \u2013 [[Kenny Stills]] \u2013 1 reception, 76 yards, TD\n}}\n\n===Standings===\n\n====Division====\n{{2013 NFC South standings|team=TB}}\n\n====Conference====\n{{2013 NFC standings|team=TB}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official website|http://www.buccaneers.com}}\n\n{{Tampa Bay Buccaneers}}\n{{Tampa Bay Buccaneers seasons}}\n{{2013 NFL season by team}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:2013 Tampa Bay Buccaneers Season}}\n[[Category:2013 in sports in Florida|Tampa Bay Buccaneers season]]\n[[Category:2013 National Football League season by team|Tampa Bay Buccaneers]]\n[[Category:21st century in Tampa, Florida]]\n[[Category:Tampa Bay Buccaneers seasons]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox NFL season\n| logo =\n| team = Tampa Bay Buccaneers\n| year = 2013\n| record = 4\u201312\n| division_place = 4th [[NFC South]]\n| coach = [[Greg Schiano]]\n| owner = [[Malcolm Glazer]]\n| general manager = [[Mark Dominik]]\n| stadium = [[Raymond James Stadium]]\n| playoffs = ''Did not qualify''\n| pro bowlers = DT [[Gerald McCoy]], CB [[Darrelle Revis]]\n| uniform=File:NFCS-Uniform-TB.png\n| colors=Red, Pewter, Black, White, Florida Orange (medium shade)\n{{color box|#b20032}} {{color box|#89765f}} {{color box|black}} {{color box|white}} {{color box|#ff7a00}} \n| shortnavlink = Buccaneers seasons\n}}\nThe [[2013 NFL season|2013 season]] was the [[Tampa Bay Buccaneers]]' 38th in the [[National Football League]], and second under [[List of Tampa Bay Buccaneers head coaches|head coach]] [[Greg Schiano]]. It also marked the 19th and final season under the ownership of [[Malcolm Glazer]], who died on May 28, 2014. The Buccaneers finished with a record of 4\u201312 and failed to improve their 7\u20139 record from last season, and were eliminated from postseason contention in Week 13. For the first time since 1996, longtime cornerback Ronde Barber was not on the roster, as he retired in May 2013.\n\nDespite having a +10 turnover margin (tied for 3rd best in the NFL), and franchise rookie quarterback records from third round [[2013 NFL Draft|draft]] pick [[Mike Glennon]], the overall offensive production ranked near the bottom of the league in most categories. The team ranked 32nd (last) in total yards, 32nd (last) in passing yards, 30th in total points scored. The team also had the third-most penalties in the league (121 for 1,136 yards), and ranked 31st in third down conversions. Running back [[Doug Martin (running back)|Doug Martin]] went on injured reserve halfway through the season with a shoulder injury. His replacement, [[Bobby Rainey]] had a solid performance, scoring his first career touchdown, and setting a franchise record for longest touchdown run (80 yards). On the defensive side, the offseason news was highlighted by the free agent acquisition of [[Darrelle Revis]], and [[Lavonte David]]'s stellar numbers.\n\n{{TOC limit|3}}\n\n==Season==\nThe team got off to a dismal start, which created considerable tension inside and outside the locker room, as well as among fans. The fan support of head coach Greg Schiano began to decay, as illustrated by a local radio station erecting a billboard carrying the message \"Fire Schiano.\"<ref>[http://espn.go.com/nfl/story/_/id/9872198/fire-schiano-billboard-appears-tampa-bay-buccaneers-winless Sign calls for Greg Schiano's firing, ESPN.com]</ref> The trouble started on opening day, as Tampa Bay had a last-second loss to the Jets, owing primarily to a personal foul late hit penalty, which advanced the Jets into field goal range, and an improbable comeback victory. Late-game losses to New Orleans, Arizona, and Seattle brought the Buccaneers to an 0\u20138 start. The Buccaneers won four of their next five games, but were ultimately eliminated from playoff contention by December, and they dropped the last three games.\n\nOne day after the conclusion of the regular season, head coach Greg Schiano and general manager Mark Dominik were fired.\n\nFor the first time since 2009, all eight regular season home games were announced as a \"sellout,\" and no regular season games were blacked out locally. Due to the new concussion rule, the Bucs did not wear their \"creamsicle\" throwback uniforms at all during this season.\n\n[[Darrelle Revis]] was named the ''[[Sporting News]]'' [[National Football League Comeback Player of the Year Award#Sporting News Comeback Player of the Year award|Comeback Player of the Year]].\n\n===Josh Freeman benching===\nThe season started out on a rocky note, as reports of a rift between head coach [[Greg Schiano]] and starting quarterback [[Josh Freeman]] were coming from the locker room. Freeman was entering the final season of his contract, and trade rumors were already being tossed around by media and fans. An allegation surfaced that Schiano rigged the voting for [[National Football League team captains|team captains]], which prevented Freeman from being selected by his teammates.<ref name=\"ESPN 9-13-13\">{{cite news|url=http://espn.go.com/nfl/story/_/id/9664746/greg-schiano-tampa-bay-buccaneers-josh-freeman-overslept-missed-photo|title=Josh Freeman overslept for photo|publisher=ESPN.com|first=Pat|last=Yasinskas|date=September 13, 2013|accessdate=September 13, 2013}}</ref> The next day, Freeman missed the annual team photo session, an absence he blamed on \"oversleeping.\"<ref name=\"ESPN 9-13-13\"/> After starting the season 0\u20133, Freeman was quickly criticized for his poor offensive output, throwing a league-worst 45.3% completion percentage, two interceptions, and only two touchdown passes.<ref name=\"USAToday\">{{cite news |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/nfl/buccaneers/2013/09/25/bucs-bench-josh-freeman-for-mike-glennon-starting-quarterback-greg-schiano-trade-general-manager-mark-dominik/2867585/|title=Bucs bench Josh Freeman, then put him on the market|publisher=USA Today|first=Jim|last=Corbett|date=September 25, 2013|accessdate=September 25, 2013}}</ref> It was also leaked that Freeman was a stage one participant in the NFL drug program,<ref>{{cite news |url=http://espn.go.com/nfl/story/_/id/9750827/josh-freeman-tampa-bay-buccaneers-nfl-drug-program|title=Sources: Bucs QB not facing penalty|publisher=ESPN.com|first=Chris|last=Mortensen|date=October 1, 2013|accessdate=October 1, 2013}}</ref> a situation related to his treatment of [[Attention deficit hyperactivity disorder|ADHD]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.620wdae.com/pages/bucs.html?article=11697903|title=Josh Freeman Releases Statement Following Report|publisher=WDAE|date=September 30, 2013|accessdate=September 30, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131003025355/http://www.620wdae.com/pages/bucs.html?article=11697903|archive-date=October 3, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> On week four, Freeman was benched in favor of rookie [[Mike Glennon]],<ref name=\"USAToday\"/> and on October 3, 2013, Freeman was released from the team as he granted.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://espn.go.com/nfl/story/_/id/9764541/tampa-bay-buccaneers-release-josh-freeman|title=Bucs release Josh Freeman|publisher=ESPN.com|date=October 3, 2013|accessdate=October 3, 2013}}</ref>\n\n===MRSA outbreak===\nDuring [[Training camp (National Football League)|training camp]], an outbreak of [[Methicillin-resistant Staphylococcus aureus|MRSA]] was reported in the Tampa Bay locker room. [[Carl Nicks (American football)|Carl Nicks]] and [[Lawrence Tynes]] contracted the infection over the summer. Nicks missed several games, while Tynes was placed on the non-football [[injured reserve list]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.myfoxtampabay.com/story/23283519/2013/08/28/tynes-not-responding-to-treatment-for-mrsa-wife-says|title=Tynes not responding to treatment for MRSA, wife says|last=Cascio|first=Josh|date=August 28, 2013|publisher=FOX 13 News|accessdate=29 August 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://espn.go.com/nfl/story/_/id/9814988/johnthan-banks-tampa-bay-buccaneers-no-risk-transmit-mrsa-others-league-says|title=Johnthan Banks cleared to play|publisher=ESPN.com|date=October 13, 2013|accessdate=October 14, 2013}}</ref> After a third player, [[Johnthan Banks]], was diagnosed in early October, the week 6 games against the [[Philadelphia Eagles|Eagles]] was in jeopardy of postponement, due to concerns over transmission. However, it was held as scheduled after medical specialists and [[National Football League Players Association|NFLPA]] representatives inspected the facility.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.cbssports.com/nfl/eye-on-football/24072908/eagles-buccaneers-game-a-go-despite-latest-mrsa-outbreak |title=Eagles-Buccaneers game a go despite latest MRSA outbreak|publisher=CBS Sports|first=Ryan|last=Wilson|date=October 12, 2013|accessdate=October 14, 2013}}</ref>\n\n==2013 Draft class==\n{{main article|2013 NFL Draft}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Round !! Selection !! Player !! Position !! College\n|-\n! 2 || 43\n| [[Johnthan Banks]] || [[Cornerback]] || [[Mississippi State Bulldogs football|Mississippi State]]\n|-\n! 3 || 73\n| [[Mike Glennon]] || [[Quarterback]] || [[NC State Wolfpack football|North Carolina State]]\n|-\n! 4 || 100\n| [[Akeem Spence]] || [[Defensive tackle]] || [[Illinois Fighting Illini football|Illinois]]\n|-\n! 4 || 126\n| [[William Gholston]] || [[Defensive end]] || [[Michigan State Spartans football|Michigan State]]\n|-\n! 5 || 147\n| [[Steven Means]] || [[Defensive end]] || [[Buffalo Bulls football|Buffalo]]\n|-\n! 6 || 189\n| [[Mike James (American football)|Mike James]] || [[Running Back (American football)|Running back]] || [[Miami Hurricanes football|Miami (FL)]]\n|}\n\n===Trades===\n* The Buccaneers acquired an additional 2013 seventh-round pick (226th overall) that sent defensive tackle [[Brian Price (American football, born 1989)|Brian Price]] to the [[Chicago Bears]] on July 26, 2012. \n* The Buccaneers later traded that same additional 2013 seventh-round pick (226th overall) that was acquired by the Bears, along with cornerback [[Aqib Talib]], to the [[New England Patriots]] in exchange for a 2013 fourth-round pick (126th overall) on November 1, 2012. \n*Tampa Bay traded [[Arrelious Benn]] and a seventh-round pick to [[Philadelphia Eagles|Philadelphia]] in exchange for the Eagles' 2013 sixth-round pick (196th overall) and a conditional draft pick in 2014.\n*Tampa Bay traded their first-round pick (13th overall) and a conditional fourth-round pick in 2014, to the [[New York Jets|Jets]] in exchange for [[Darrelle Revis]].\n*Tampa Bay traded their fourth-round selection (112th overall) and their sixth-round selection (181st overall) to [[Oakland Raiders|Oakland]] in exchange for the Raiders' fourth-round selection (100th overall) in order to draft [[Akeem Spence]] on the third day of the [[2013 NFL Draft]].\n*Tampa Bay traded [[LeGarrette Blount]] to [[New England Patriots|New England]] for [[Jeff Demps]] and a seventh-round selection (229th overall).\n*Tampa Bay traded their sixth-round selection (196th overall) and their seven-round selection (229th overall) to [[Minnesota Vikings|Minnesota]] for a sixth-round selection (189th overall) in order to draft [[Mike James (American football)|Mike James]] on the third day of the 2013 NFL Draft.\n*Tampa Bay traded their 2014 sixth-round selection to [[Chicago Bears|Chicago]] for [[Gabe Carimi]].\n\n==Staff==\n{{NFL final staff\n|Year=2013\n|TeamName=Tampa Bay Buccaneers\n|BC1=#b20032\n|FC1=white\n|BDC1=#89765f\n|Front Office=\n*Owner/President \u2013 [[Malcolm Glazer]]\n*Co-Chairman \u2013 [[Bryan Glazer]]\n*Co-Chairman \u2013 [[Edward Glazer]]\n*Co-Chairman \u2013 [[Joel Glazer]]\n*General Manager \u2013 [[Mark Dominik]]\n*Director of Player Personnel \u2013 [[Dennis Hickey (American football)|Dennis Hickey]]\n*Director of College Scouting \u2013 [[Eric Stokes (American football)|Eric Stokes]]\n*Coordinator of Pro Scouting \u2013 [[Shelton Quarles]]\n*Coordinator of Football Administration \u2013 [[Mike Greenberg (American football)|Mike Greenberg]]\n*Special Assistant to the Head Coach \u2013 [[Butch Davis]]\n|Head Coaches=\n*Head Coach \u2013 [[Greg Schiano]]\n|Offensive Coaches=\n*Offensive Coordinator \u2013 [[Mike Sullivan (American football coach)|Mike Sullivan]]\n*Senior Offensive Assistant \u2013 [[Jimmy Raye II|Jimmy Raye]]\n*Quarterbacks \u2013 [[John McNulty (American football)|John McNulty]]\n*Running Backs \u2013 [[Earnest Byner]]\n*Wide Receivers \u2013[[John Garrett (football coach)|John Garrett]]\n*Tight Ends \u2013 [[Brian Angelichio]]\n*Offensive Line \u2013 [[Bob Bostad]]\n*Assistant Offensive Line \u2013 [[Steve Loney]]\n*Offensive Assistant \u2013 [[Ben McDaniels]] \n|Defensive Coaches=\n*Defensive Coordinator \u2013 [[Bill Sheridan]]\n*Assistant Defensive Coordinator \u2013 [[Bob Fraser (American football)|Bob Fraser]]\n*Defensive Line \u2013 [[Randy Melvin]]\n*Defensive Front Seven \u2013 [[Bryan Cox]]\n*Linebackers \u2013 [[Robb Smith]]\n*Defensive Backs \u2013 [[Tony Oden]]\n*Assistant Defensive Backs \u2013 [[Jeff Hafley]]\n*Defensive Assistant \u2013 [[Tem Lukabu]]\n*Quality Control to the Head Coach \u2013 [[Dan Shamash]]\n|Special Teams Coaches=\n*Special Teams Coordinator \u2013 [[Dave Wannstedt]]\n*Assistant Special Teams \u2013 [[Phil Galiano]]\n|Strength and Conditioning=\n*Head Strength and Conditioning \u2013 [[Jay Butler]]\n*Assistant Strength and Conditioning \u2013 [[Joe Vaughn]]\n*Assistant Strength and Conditioning \u2013 [[Bob Gilmartin]]\n|Coaching Assistants=\n*[[Andy Aurich]], [[Andrew Janocko]], [[Billy Miller]]\n}}\n\n==Final roster==\n{{NFL final roster\n|Year=2013\n|TeamName=Tampa Bay Buccaneers\n|BC1=#b20032\n|FC1=white\n|BDC1=#89765f\n|Active=53\n|Inactive=18\n|PS=8\n\n|Quarterbacks=\n{{NFLplayer|&nbsp;8|Mike Glennon|rookie=y}}\n{{NFLplayer|&nbsp;6|Dan Orlovsky}}\n\n|Running Backs=\n{{NFLplayer|44|Michael Hill|d=American football|rookie=y}}\n{{NFLplayer|46|Spencer Larsen|FB}}\n{{NFLplayer|30|Brian Leonard}}\n{{NFLplayer|41|Erik Lorig|FB}}\n{{NFLplayer|45|Lonnie Pryor|rookie=y|FB/RB}}\n{{NFLplayer|43|Bobby Rainey}}\n\n|Wide Receivers=\n{{NFLplayer|18|Skye Dawson|rookie=y}}\n{{NFLplayer|83|Vincent Jackson}}\n{{NFLplayer|80|Chris Owusu}}\n{{NFLplayer|17|Eric Page}}\n{{NFLplayer|11|Tiquan Underwood}}\n\n|Tight Ends=\n{{NFLplayer|86|Kyle Adams}}\n{{NFLplayer|81|Tim Wright|d=American football|rookie=y}}\n\n|Offensive Linemen=\n{{NFLplayer|72|Gabe Carimi|T}}\n{{NFLplayer|69|Demar Dotson|T}}\n{{NFLplayer|75|Davin Joseph|G}}\n{{NFLplayer|62|Ted Larsen|C}}\n{{N