rs=[[Kevin Burkhardt]], [[John Lynch (American football)|John Lynch]] and [[Erin Andrews]]\n |reference=[http://www.nfl.com/gamecenter/2013090807/2013/REG1/buccaneers@jets Recap], [http://www.nfl.com/liveupdate/gamecenter/55846/NYJ_Gamebook.pdf Game book]\n |scoring=\n'''First quarter'''\n*NYJ \u2013 [[Josh Freeman]] fumble out of bounds in end zone for a safety, 8:35. ''Jets 2\u20130.''\n*TB - [[Mike Williams (wide receiver, born 1987)|Mike Williams]] 17-yard pass from Josh Freeman ([[Rian Lindell]] kick), 1:07. ''Buccaneers 7\u20132. '''Drive: 5 plays, 44 yards, 2:39.'''''\n'''Second quarter'''\n*NYJ \u2013 [[Nick Folk]] 43-yard field goal, 11:01. ''Buccaneers 7\u20135. '''Drive: 13 plays, 55 yards, 5:06.'''''\n*TB \u2013 [[Doug Martin (running back)|Doug Martin]] 5-yard run (Rian Lindell kick), 6:46. ''Buccaneers 14\u20135. '''Drive: 1 play, 5 yards, 0:05.'''''\n*NYJ \u2013 [[Kellen Winslow II|Kellen Winslow]] 7-yard pass from [[Geno Smith]] (Nick Folk kick), 0:34. ''Buccaneers 14\u201312. '''Drive: 6 plays, 31 yards, 1:59.'''''\n'''Third quarter'''\n* ''No scoring plays.''\n'''Fourth quarter'''\n*NYJ \u2013 Nick Folk 30-yard field goal, 5:05. ''Jets 15\u201314. '''Drive: 14 plays, 65 yards, 6:20.'''''\n*TB \u2013 Rian Lindell 37-yard field goal, 0:34. ''Buccaneers 17\u201315. '''Drive: 9 plays, 61 yards, 1:40.'''''\n*NYJ \u2013 Nick Folk 48-yard field goal, 0:02. ''Jets 18\u201317. '''Drive: 5 plays, 50 yards, 0:32.'''''\n |stats=\n'''Top passers'''\n*TB \u2013 [[Josh Freeman]] \u2013 15/31, 210 yards, TD, INT\n*NYJ \u2013 [[Geno Smith]] \u2013 24/38, 256 yards, TD, INT\n'''Top rushers'''\n*TB \u2013 [[Doug Martin (running back)|Doug Martin]] \u2013 24 rushes, 65 yards, TD\n*NYJ \u2013 [[Geno Smith]] \u2013 6 rushes, 47 yards\n'''Top receivers'''\n*TB \u2013 [[Vincent Jackson]] \u2013 7 receptions, 154 yards\n*NYJ \u2013 [[Kellen Winslow II|Kellen Winslow]] \u2013 7 receptions, 79 yards, TD\n}}\nTampa Bay took the lead 17\u201315 with a [[Rian Lindell]] field goal with 34 seconds remaining. However, on the ensuing [[New York Jets|Jets]] drive, Jets rookie quarterback [[Geno Smith]] scrambled for a 10-yard run to the right sideline. A personal foul penalty was called on [[Lavonte David]] of the Buccaneers for a late hit out-of-bounds, which advanced the Jets to the Buccaneers 30-yard line. With 2 seconds left in regulation, [[Nick Folk]] kicked a 48-yard field goal, and the Jets won the game 18\u201317.\n\n====Week 2: vs. New Orleans Saints====\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle={{NFLPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers 97thru13|border=2}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week Two: New Orleans Saints at Tampa Bay Buccaneers&nbsp;\u2013 Game summary\n |date=September 15\n |time=4:05 p.m. EDT\n |road='''Saints'''\n |R1=10|R2=0|R3=3|R4=3\n |home=Buccaneers\n |H1=7|H2=0|H3=0|H4=7\n |stadium=Raymond James Stadium, [[Tampa, Florida]]\n |attendance=60,870\n |weather=Cloudy, {{convert|93|F|C}}\n |referee=[[Bill Leavy]]\n |TV=Fox\n |TVAnnouncers=Kevin Burkhardt, John Lynch and Erin Andrews\n |reference=[http://www.nfl.com/gamecenter/2013091510/2013/REG2/saints@buccaneers Recap], [http://www.nfl.com/liveupdate/gamecenter/55864/TB_Gamebook.pdf Game book]\n |scoring=\n'''First quarter'''\n*NO \u2013 [[Garrett Hartley]] 44-yard field goal, 10:30. ''Saints 3\u20130. '''Drive: 11 plays, 54 yards, 4:30.'''''\n*TB \u2013 [[Kevin Ogletree]] 5-yard pass from [[Josh Freeman]] ([[Rian Lindell]] kick), 5:15. ''Buccaneers 7\u20133. '''Drive: 7 plays, 35 yards, 2:48.'''''\n*NO \u2013 [[Jimmy Graham]] 56-yard pass from [[Drew Brees]] (Garrett Hartley kick), 2:36. ''Saints 10\u20137. '''Drive: 6 plays, 80 yards, 2:39.'''''\n'''Second quarter'''\n* ''No scoring plays.''\n'''Third quarter'''\n*NO \u2013 Garrett Hartley 41-yard field goal, 8:04. ''Saints 13\u20137. '''Drive: 8 plays, 17 yards, 3:45.'''''\n'''Fourth quarter'''\n*TB \u2013 [[Mason Foster]] 85-yard interception return (Rian Lindell kick), 12:40. ''Buccaneers 14\u201313.''\n*NO \u2013 Garrett Hartley 27-yard field goal, 0:00. ''Saints 16\u201314. '''Drive: 5 plays, 54 yards, 1:06.'''''\n |stats=\n'''Top passers'''\n*NO \u2013 [[Drew Brees]] \u2013 26/46, 322 yards, TD, 2 INT\n*TB \u2013 [[Josh Freeman]] \u2013 9/22, 125 yards, TD, INT\n'''Top rushers'''\n*NO \u2013 [[Pierre Thomas (American football)|Pierre Thomas]] \u2013 5 rushes, 29 yards\n*TB \u2013 [[Doug Martin (running back)|Doug Martin]] \u2013 29 rushes, 144 yards\n'''Top receivers'''\n*NO \u2013 [[Jimmy Graham]] \u2013 10 receptions, 179 yards, TD\n*TB \u2013 [[Vincent Jackson]] \u2013 5 receptions, 77 yards\n}}\nTampa Bay took the lead 14\u201313 after an 85-yard interception return by [[Mason Foster]] with just under 13 minutes remaining. In the closing minutes the Buccaneers drove to the New Orleans 29 yard line, and attempted a field goal with 1:10 left. The kick missed, and the Saints took over with just over one minute left. [[Drew Brees]] drove the Saints to the Tampa Bay 9 yard line in three plays, and [[Garrett Hartley]] kicked the game-winning field goal as time expired.\n\n====Week 3: at New England Patriots====\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle={{NFLPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers 97thru13|border=2}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week Three: Tampa Bay Buccaneers at New England Patriots&nbsp;\u2013 Game summary\n |date=September 22\n |time=1:00 p.m. EDT\n |road=Buccaneers\n |R1=3|R2=0|R3=0|R4=0\n |home='''Patriots'''\n |H1=0|H2=17|H3=3|H4=3\n |stadium=[[Gillette Stadium]], [[Foxborough, Massachusetts]]\n |attendance=68,756\n |weather=Sunny, {{convert|65|F|C}}\n |referee=[[Jeff Triplette]]\n |TV=Fox\n |TVAnnouncers=Kevin Burkhardt, John Lynch and Erin Andrews\n |reference=[http://www.nfl.com/gamecenter/2013092206/2013/REG3/buccaneers@patriots Recap], [http://www.nfl.com/liveupdate/gamecenter/55875/NE_Gamebook.pdf Game book]\n |scoring=\n'''First quarter'''\n*TB \u2013 [[Rian Lindell]] 30-yard field goal, 1:47. ''Buccaneers 3\u20130. '''