e second half to tie the game and force overtime. Tampa Bay won the coin toss in overtime, but went 3-and-out on their first possession. Seattle kicked a field goal on the next possession, completing their greatest comeback (21 points) in franchise history.\n\nThis loss dropped the Buccaneers to 0\u20138 on the season, a feat shared with the [[2013 Jacksonville Jaguars season|Jacksonville Jaguars]].\n\n====Week 10: vs. Miami Dolphins====\n\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle={{NFLPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers 97thru13|border=2}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week Ten: Miami Dolphins at Tampa Bay Buccaneers&nbsp;\u2013 Game summary\n |date=November 11\n |time=8:40 p.m. EST\n |road=Dolphins\n |R1=0|R2=7|R3=12|R4=0\n |home='''Buccaneers'''\n |H1=10|H2=5|H3=0|H4=7\n |stadium=Raymond James Stadium, Tampa, Florida\n |attendance=64,448\n |weather=Sunny, {{convert|73|F|C}}\n |referee=Jeff Triplette\n |TV=[[Monday Night Football|ESPN]]\n |TVAnnouncers=[[Mike Tirico]], [[Jon Gruden]] and [[Lisa Salters]]\n |reference=[http://www.nfl.com/gamecenter/2013111100/2013/REG10/dolphins@buccaneers Recap], [http://www.nfl.com/liveupdate/gamecenter/55983/TB_Gamebook.pdf Game book]\n |scoring=\n'''First quarter'''\n*TB \u2013 [[Donald Penn]] 1-yard pass from [[Mike Glennon]] ([[Rian Lindell]] kick), 9:37. ''Buccaneers 7\u20130. '''Drive: 9 plays, 76 yards, 5:23.'''''\n*TB \u2013 Rian Lindell 24-yard field goal, 5:27. ''Buccaneers 10\u20130. '''Drive: 6 plays, 34 yards, 2:40.'''''\n'''Second quarter'''\n*TB \u2013 [[Daniel Thomas (American football)|Daniel Thomas]] tackled in the end zone by [[Lavonte David]] for a safety, 13:52. ''Buccaneers 12\u20130.''\n*TB \u2013 Rian Lindell 35-yard field goal, 9:01. ''Buccaneers 15\u20130. '''Drive: 8 plays, 41 yards, 4:51.'''''\n*MIA \u2013 [[Rishard Matthews]] 6-yard pass from [[Ryan Tannehill]] ([[Caleb Sturgis]] kick), 0:28. ''Buccaneers 15\u20137. '''Drive: 9 plays, 90 yards, 3:26.'''''\n'''Third quarter'''\n*MIA \u2013